The paper proposes a deep neural network approach for identifying characteristic metabolic patterns for early differential diagnosis of parkinsonian syndromes using PET imaging. This involves both compression and classification parts, which are trained using labelled and unlabelled data. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and bioinformatics (cs.BIO) sub-categories.
